Hello,
My team has been successfully using the Omio X8 for the past season, and we are about to buy another machine. Are there any better alternatives for sheet metal that have better work holding solutions? Also maybe better tool changing and zeroing? We have about $4500 to play with. I need a link by tomorrow.

Thanks in advance!

In that budget, I don’t have much else that comes to mind. However, you are pretty close to the price of the new Langmuir MR-1, which looks pretty decent in their videos. You might want to check it out.

Or, maybe you want to consider other types of equipment, like a bending brake, or other things you might need.
